<title>XHTML Functional -- OBJECT - VSPACE</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>The PNG images, which are contained in a object element, have

been assigned the VSPACE attribute. VSPACE adds white space above

and below the image. The first image has been assigned a value of

40 pixels; the second image has been assign 80 pixels.</p>



<object data="../images/trucks.png" type="image/png" vspace="40">A

maze graphic should be displayed.</object> VSPACE is used to add

white space above and below the image. The graphic to the left of

this paragraph has VSPACE set to 40 pixels. <br />

 <object data="../images/trucks.png" vspace="80">A maze graphic should

be displayed.</object> VSPACE is used to add white space above and

below the image. The graphic to the left of this paragraph has

VSPACE set to 80 pixels. 

